        "tier": "DOMAIN",
        "title": "Powerhouse Software Architecture",
        "createdAt": "2026-03-30T19:20:00.000Z",
        "description": "Document models as core unit across three layers: Data Infrastructure (Reactor), Host Application (Connect/Switchboard/Fusion), Customization.",
        "orientation": "Powerhouse's software architecture is built around document models as the fundamental unit of data and workflow. Everything \u2014 storage, sync, editing, and customization \u2014 operates on documents. The architecture separates into three layers: the Data Infrastructure Layer (Reactor nodes with pluggable storage adapters), the Host Application Layer (Connect, Switchboard, Fusion, Renown, and Academy as plugin-driven shells), and the Customization Layer (organization-specific instances and plugins). This layered approach means contributors work with tailored tools while sharing common infrastructure. The Reactor handles sync and storage, host apps provide the UI shells, and plugins turn them into purpose-built platforms."
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:49.000Z"
    }
  },
